messages.message:
Hey Sabya! When I ran unit tests last week in apps-server with `make build mypy` and `make test`, everything worked. But I think something changed in webserver (specifically this pr (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/29650)) that made the tests and its build break, and now i'm having trouble rebuilding due to the below error if i run `make test`
``` error: Incompatible types in assignment (expression has type "instabase.apps_server.server.config.BaseConfig", variable has type "instabase.server.config.BaseConfig")```
and this error when i run `make build mypy`
```instabase/table_utils/tableclient_grpc.py:372: error: "TableServiceStub" has no attribute "InsertBulk"```
Do you know what might be up here?
Can you try to do a `make clean`?

The second one is separate from the first, that’s from my team’s thrift to grpc migration. Yan, @Victor Zeng @Cheryl Zhou can you help take a look at InsertBulk. That was renamed to InsertBatch, so either Junwon’s build folders didn’t get cleaned, or we forgot to update a stub somewhere.

it's weird that i am having some trouble finding `table_utils/tableclient_grpc.py` but i do see that we have a stub called InsertBatch in TableServiceStub (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/shared-utils/py-utils/typing-utils/src/py/stubs/instabase/protos/table_service/table_service_pb2_grpc.pyi#L51). Did `make clean` work for you? @Junwon Jang
Just tried `make clean` and the second issue no longer exists from my side as well.

I will need to take a look. This was something I had to change and the change to from instabase.server import config, even if it works is not thr right fix. Will take a look at this IST daytime.

Is there a Jenkins pipeline I can use to execute this test?
Actually, I can pass the first case after make clean.
So just so I understand, after make clean you don't need to make that import change either?
Yes Sabya! Let’s wait @Junwon Jang  to validate from his side
ah nice that fixed it for me as well thanks everyone!
